### Pools
- Rocks
- CO2 dissolved in ocean
- In living things (mostly plants)
- In soil (organic matter, non-decomposed)
	- Recycled by microbial respiration/decomposition
- CO2 in the atmosphere
	-  Currently 890Pg C in the atmosphere (~416ppm)
		- Pg = 10^15g, 10^12kg, Trillion tons
- Fossil fuel deposits

### Sources and contributing factors
 - More CO2 in atmosphere
	- Burning fossil fuels
	- Increases amount in oceans as well
		- Causes acidification
- Cattle farming contributes significant amounts of methane (CH4) to the atmosphere
	- Because their stomachs ferment material using endosymbiotes, unlike [[Unsorted/Humans\|human]] digestion
- Weakening sinks
	- [[Unsorted/Deforestation\|Deforestation]]
	- Land use changes
- Use of limestone (part of concrete) releases CO2
	- Smaller amount



### Sinks
- Plants
	- ![Pasted image 20220830195049.png|175](data:image/png;base64,)
	- Oscillation due to summer/winter in northern hemisphere (more biomass)
- The ocean can absorb CO2, concentration is increasing
- Soil can also absorb CO2
- Soil and ocean sinks are increasing capacity
	- Plants in deforested areas are able to grow faster due to increased atmospheric CO2 and reduced competition

# Influence of [[Unsorted/Climate change\|Climate change]]

- Primary cause of climate change is the combustion of fossil fuels
- [[Unsorted/Humans\|Human]] activity has also damaged carbon sinks
